LAB 02 — Multi-Stage Docker Build Optimization Lab 

 

Shrink container image sizes by up to 90% using advanced Dockerfile patterns 

Difficulty 

Intermediate 

Estimated Time 

3–5 hours 

Tools Required 

Docker, dive, Trivy, GitHub Actions, GHCR 

 

Overview 

Start with a bloated 1.2GB Node.js application image and systematically reduce it to under 120MB using multi-stage builds, distroless base images, BuildKit cache mounts, and proper .dockerignore configuration. Then automate size regression detection and vulnerability scanning in CI. 

WHY THIS MATTERS IN 2025 

Image bloat costs real money in registry storage and pod startup latency. At scale, a 1GB versus 100MB image means minutes of additional pod startup time during traffic spikes. Multi-stage builds and image optimization are common interview questions at FAANG-tier companies. 
